CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 5, 1961, page A14, reads: "The 'Tan' Goddesses," members of the recently organized professional models' club, are shown at one of their organizational meetings, Left to right: Janie Ross (Earl Wheeler graduate), sponsor of the group; Valaida Coleman (Earl Wheeler), president; Lucretia Tabb (Grace Del Marco in New York), financial secretary; Alberta Thompson (John Robert Powers), treasurer; Catherine Tabb (Grace Del Marco) and Jessie Williams (Earl Wheeler). Marlene Moore, fashion editor for The Courier, is fashion coordinator and adviser, and Yvonne Kemp is choreographer. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: "Tan Goddesses" models, including from left: Janie Ross, Valaida Coleman, Lucretia Tabb, Alberta Thompson, Catherine Tabb, and Jessie Williams, and unknown posed on sofa in interior with profile portrait relief decorations on wall
